Definition: not liable to error in judgment or action
Example: most surefooted of the statesmen who dealt with the depression- Walter Lippman; demonstrates a surefooted storytelling talent- Michiko Kakutani
Synonyms: surefooted, sure-footed, not, liable, to, error, in, judgment, or, action, most, of, the, statesmen, who, dealt, with, depression, -, Walter, Lippman, demonstrates, a, storytelling, talent, Michiko, Kakutani
Category: adj.all
